Post-reformation Catholic polyphonic motets.  Philips was English, but was an exile on account of his religion. 

This recording is substantially better than the one on the Hyperion label (Holman / Winchester CC), in terms of both authenticity and tone: the Tudor Consort is New Zealand's answer to the Tallis Scholars.  

